data.enText: a person who pays money, usually once a year, to receive regular copies of a magazine or newspaper
a person who gives money regularly to help the work of an organization such as a charity
data.chText: （慈善机关等的）定期捐款者，定期捐助者

data.enText: a person who pays to receive a service

word_means: 定期捐款者，定期捐助者

means: (慈善机关等的)定期捐款者，定期捐助者

tr: someone who contributes (or promises to contribute) a sum of money
someone who contracts to receive and pay for a service or a certain number of issues of a publication

example.ex: I have been a subscriber to Railway Magazine for many years.
example.tran: 我订阅《铁路杂志》已有很多年了。

value.def: A magazine's or a newspaper's subscribers are the people who pay to receive copies of it regularly.
value.tran: (杂志或报纸的)订阅人，订购者，订户

example.ex: China has almost 15 million subscribers to satellite and cable television.
example.tran: 中国有将近 1,500 万卫星电视和有线电视用户。

value.def: Subscribers to a service are the people who pay to receive the service.
The subscribers to a charity, campaign, or organization are the people who support it by sending money regularly to it.
value.tran: (慈善机构、活动的)定期捐款者，定期捐助者;(组织的)定期缴费者，会员
